quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  40,34,"Joseph came to you before with clear signs, but you never ceased to doubt the message he brought you. When he died, you said, 'God will not send another messenger.'\"\" In this way God leaves the transgressors and doubters to go astray"
  40,35,those who dispute God's revelations without any authority are doing something that is greatly abhorrent to God and to the believers. That is how God seals up the heart of every arrogant oppressor
  40,36,"Pharaoh said, \"O Haman, build for me a lofty building so that I may gain access"
  40,37,"to the heavens, so that I may look upon the God of Moses: I am convinced that he is a liar!\" That is how Pharaoh's evil actions were made to look fair in the eyes of Pharoah, and he was turned away from the path [of truth]. Pharaoh's scheming led to nothing but ruin"
  40,38,"The believer said, \"My people, follow me! I will guide you to the right path"
  40,39,"O my people, the life of this world is only a temporary provision; and the Hereafter is the permanent abode"
  40,40,"Whoever does evil will be requited with evil; but whoever does good, whether male or female, and is a believer, will enter the Garden; where they will be provided for without measure"